    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "Ketchikan, Alaska",
      "Published for C.P. Johnston Company, Seattle, Wash. 98109\nthe Continental card\nKETCHIKAN is an important center for lumbering\nand fishing in Southeastern Alaska.\nIn the fore-\nground is Ketchikan International Airport on\nGravina Island. Passengers are ferried across the\nTongass Narrows to and from Ketchikan.\nB4650-Color Photo: R. W. Pickrell\n. Emerile, CA 94608\n©Mike Roberts Color Productions\n2015."
